# =====================================================================
# StrikeForge Frontend — Environment Variable Template
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# QA Issue #8 fix (CRITICAL): the frontend Firebase client SDK requires
# four `VITE_FIREBASE_*` variables at build time. Without them,
# `initializeFirebaseClient()` throws and the user can never sign in.
#
# QA Issue #9 fix (CRITICAL): the frontend api/client.ts uses absolute
# URLs sourced from `VITE_API_BASE_URL`. Without it, API calls resolve
# to relative paths against the Vite dev server (port 5173) instead of
# the backend (port 3000) — vite.config.ts deliberately omits a /api
# proxy so that local CORS behavior matches production.
#
# Vite exposes only `VITE_*`-prefixed variables to the browser bundle —
# any other prefix is stripped at build time (documented Vite behavior).
#
# Usage:
#   cp frontend/.env.example frontend/.env
#   Then fill in values. The committed example carries safe local-dev
#   defaults (the Firebase Auth emulator accepts any apiKey because it
#   does not validate; the project ID must match docker-compose.yml's
#   FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID for the emulator to issue tokens consumable by
#   the backend's firebase-admin verifier).
# =====================================================================

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_API_BASE_URL (REQUIRED for cross-origin api/client.ts calls)
#   Consumer: frontend/src/api/client.ts (request() helper).
#   When set, every relative API path (e.g., /api/designs) is rewritten
#   to an absolute URL prefixed by this base. When unset, requests are
#   sent as relative paths (which fail in dev because Vite has no /api
#   proxy by design — see vite.config.ts §44-47).
#   Local dev default: http://localhost:3000
#   Production: set to the backend's public URL (e.g.,
#   https://api.strikeforge.app).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY (REQUIRED)
#   Consumer: frontend/src/auth/firebase-client.ts.
#   For the local Firebase Auth emulator, this can be any non-empty
#   string — the emulator does not validate the key. In production
#   this must be the real Firebase Web API key from the project
#   console (it is NOT a secret — it identifies the project, and
#   security is enforced server-side via Firebase Security Rules and
#   the backend's `verifyIdToken()` per Rule R3).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=local-emulator-key

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN (REQUIRED)
#   Consumer: frontend/src/auth/firebase-client.ts.
#   The OAuth sign-in domain. For the local emulator a placeholder
#   value is acceptable because the emulator branch of init bypasses
#   the OAuth domain. In production this must be
#   `<project-id>.firebaseapp.com`.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=strikeforge-local.firebaseapp.com

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID (REQUIRED)
#   Consumer: frontend/src/auth/firebase-client.ts.
#   MUST match the backend's FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID (set in
#   docker-compose.yml as `strikeforge-local`) so that ID tokens
#   issued by the emulator carry the same `aud` claim that the
#   backend's `firebase-admin.verifyIdToken()` expects.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=strikeforge-local

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID (REQUIRED)
#   Consumer: frontend/src/auth/firebase-client.ts.
#   App-specific identifier. For the local emulator any non-empty
#   string is acceptable. In production this is the Web App ID from
#   the Firebase project console (e.g.,
#   `1:123456789012:web:abc123def456`).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:000000000000:web:0000000000000000000000

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID (OPTIONAL)
#   Optional — only required when Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) is
#   configured. The configurator does NOT use FCM; safe to leave
#   unset.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET (OPTIONAL)
#   Optional — only used by the Firebase JS SDK's Storage module. The
#   configurator uploads logos via the BACKEND's GCS service (per
#   Rule R3, the frontend never touches Firebase Storage directly),
#   so this can be safely omitted.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
